summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2008 WHEELED COACH E-350 VAN. THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE SECONDARY BATTERY TERMINAL WAS CORRODED. AS A RESULT, THE WHEELED COACH ACCESSORY POWER CABLE WAS AFFECTED AND THE SIREN, WARNING LIGHTS AND INTERIOR COMPARTMENT LIGHTS WOULD FAIL INTERMITTENTLY OR ALL TOGETHER. THE CONTACT DID NOT TAKE THE VEHICLE TO A DEALER. THE CONTACT CALLED THE MANUFACTURER REGARDING NHTSA CAMPAIGN I.D. NUMBER: 11V470000 (EQUIPMENT:ELECTRICAL). THE MANUFACTURER ADVISED THE CONTACT THAT THE VEHICLE WAS NOT INCLUDED IN THE RECALL BASED ON THE STATE IN WHICH THE VEHICLE WAS REGISTERED. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS UNKNOWN. THE VIN WAS NOT AVAILABLE.
